When the cupola was eventually completed, it was an occasion of enough moment to warrant a long article in the <i>Irish Times</i> on Saturday, 2 July 1904. The Lord Lieutenant paid a visit and in the middle of a long speech, said:

<blockquote>&quot;... I am delighted to hear that what I may call the <b>cupola affair</b> has been happily closed, and that you have at last achieved completion of the work which no doubt for many years has been much necessitated. I think there is no doubt that in these days when we want to devote money to the most practical and useful purposes it was probably better to have a more modest scheme, costing less, and to save any money which came in in other respects for the purposes of the enlargement of the school, and adding to its yearly revenues...&quot;

Before His Excellency left the hall the Head Master at his request granted the boys a holiday in honour of the visit.</blockquote>
